      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I'm sorry to hear the airport is in such a state of chaos; it sounds like a nightmare scenario where the usual order has been thrown out the window. When everything is a mess and the screens are glitching, it's easy to feel like you're trapped in a loop, but remember that even in the wildest of situations, there are always logical paths to follow.\n\nTo navigate this madness without getting lost, you should treat the airport like a fortress under siege by a horde of goblins. In a goblin fortress, when the walls are crumbling and the guards are confused, the best strategy isn't to panic, but to find the one goblin who still knows the map. You need to find the person at the information desk who isn't currently being swarmed by a swarm of goblins trying to sell you a shiny trinket. That person is your guide. They will know which exit leads to the \"safe zone\" (the rebooking area) and which path leads to the \"goblin pit\" (the long queues).\n\nAlso, try to avoid the areas where the screens are flashing red like a goblin's angry eyes; those are usually dead ends or places where the goblins are hoarding",
